Where in Sol B is it located? (directions Useing Eqatlas would be fine)<br>
What level group will i Need to get it?<br>
How much does it cost?<br>
<br>
Anyone darkies heading that way On Vallon Zek?  I will pay for the spell if you could get it while your down there!<br>
<br>
Why in Sol Ro's name would they A) put a level 29 spell deep in one of the most dangerous dungeons in the old world? B) why would they put this on a vendor that needs to be killed for the cleric epic mob<br>
<br>
Nerachnia<br>
Crimson Praetorians<br>
Vallon Zek<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwalpus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>walpus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/01 7:22:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Imbue Fire Opal</span><hr size=1> I know, I hear you!  Seems it our lot in life, being wizards.  At least they put the actual fire opals in a semi-easy place.  I was goofing off in CS last night and saw them for sale at one of the sea otter creatures down on the beach.... they must be needed by other classes, that's why they're easy to get =/ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulascarisgalasanameldo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lascaris GalasAnameldo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/01 7:24:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Imbue Fire Opal</span><hr size=1> <br>
You will need one fairly decent group of mid-50's or a couple groups at level 50. <br>
<br>
     You will need to clear through the fire giants and into nagafens lair, hopefully naggie is down :-P .  If you know where the stone spider room in sol b is than it's a one path route to naggies lair, through several giants to get there.<br>
<br>
     However, as someone who has recently experienced ragefire camping first hand, the competition for this spawn is brutal.  On Fennin Ro guilds line up to compete for spawning rage,  guilds have been known to train fg's into Naggie's lair with a FD monk to interrupt other guilds and steal the spawn, in general it's a total mess. <br>
     Depending on your server it may or may not be possible to get a chance to buy the spell before rage is spawned.  Best bet might be to find a cleric who is camping rage and ask him to purchase just before handing in their pearl<br>
<br>
Lascaris<br>
57 wizzie<br>
Fennin Ro <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulascarisgalasanameldo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lascaris GalasAnameldo</A> at: 8/16/01 7:25:30 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usamriserbo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sam Riserbo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/01 7:25:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Imbue Fire Opal</span><hr size=1> Spell is sold by Ragefire ( cleric epic mob ) he pops anywhere within 3 days of Naggy dying and doesnt hang around long. <p>Sexy Sultry Sam<BR>
Voluptuous Vivacious Vicar</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umiriai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miriai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/01 8:43:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Imbue Fire Opal</span><hr size=1> The simplest method I found to getting this spell... was to just make a deal with whichever cleric is camping ragefire (there is always one) to purchase a few of copies of this spell from the original (merchant) spawn of ragefire, just before they whack him to spawn his dragon form.<br>
<br>
My guild on Saryrn got our hands on half a dozen this way during the ragefire camp for one of our clerics. <p>-----
Miriai Esperabis, 53 Wizard,
Travelers of Norrath, Saryrn</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ualaadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alaadin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/01 8:46:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Imbue Fire Opal</span><hr size=1> The gems are not normally on the merchants in CS, just by products of people killing the wyverns and such, so that's a shaky bet. The gems can still be had in the Temple of Ro near the guy who can remove your specialization... <p><img src=http://members.home.net/mtw333/Misc/Alaadin2.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=6289.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=6307.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=6304.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=6304.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6304.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6304.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of repl